In this short position paper, we describe our approach to developing a system for delivering remote services to people suffering from depression and similar mental illnesses. Our initial system architecture has two key components: a tool for helping the consumer and their carers develop and manage her care plan, and .a consumercontrolled consent control and management tool. We believe that the former will give the consumer much-needed control over their long-term care, and that the latter will support the development of the userâ€™s trust in the system. Author